<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 275 Engine Diagnostics Manual - Engine Symptoms Diagnostics - Test Procedures - ECM Reset/IDM Reset
        (Intermittent Engine Stumble)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s305010402.7" svcproctype="diagnose" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ECM Reset/IDM Reset (Intermittent Engine Stumble)</title>
        <svcprocinfo id="s305010402.7.1">
            <table id="t305010405" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Indications</title>
                <tgroup cols="1">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>WAIT TO START lamp cycles ON while engine running</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Glow plugs recycle while engine running</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Engine stumbles and dies</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Loss of accelerator pedal authority</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row rowsep="0">
                            <entry>
                                <para>Miles driven are not logged if ECM reset occurs during current key cycle</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
            <table id="t305010406" type="simple" frame="topbot">
                <title>Causes</title>
                <tgroup cols="2">
                    <colspec colname="col1"/>
                    <colspec colname="col2"/>
                    <tbody>
                        <row>
                            <entry morerows="3">
                                <para>An Electronic Control Module (ECM) reset occurs when the ECM momentarily reboots
                                    or is turned OFF and ON while the engine is operating.
                                </para>
                                <para>If a reset occurs, the engine will momentarily stumble and the ECM will go through
                                    a normal KEY ON cycle. This includes:
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Illuminate the WAIT TO START lamp</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Enable glow plugs</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Enable Inlet Air Heater (IAH)</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Validate the accelerator pedal position</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry morerows="6">
                                <para>If the pedal is not at idle position when the reset occurs, a DTC is set and
                                    engine speed goes to low idle. The ECM will not allow accelerator pedal authority
                                    until the Accelerator Pedal Sensor (APS) is released.
                                </para>
                                <para>Momentary loss of power to the ECM or IDM may be caused by:</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Poor fuse connection</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Intermittent open at connectors</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Poor battery power feed harness connection</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Poor ground connection</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Poor power relay connection</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Open power or ground circuit</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>-</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Poor module connection, corrosion, or water inclusion</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc id="s305010402.7.2">
            <title>Diagnostics for Engine Stumble</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using the EST, check for DTCs for both the engine and chassis modules.</para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>If DTC 626 (unexpected reset fault) or 534 (IDM relay voltage low) are present as active
                            or inactive codes, continue with step 4.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If any other engine DTCs are active, perform appropriate diagnostics and repairs before
                            continuing with these procedures.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>If any chassis DTCs are active when checking the Electronic System Controller (ESC),
                            perform appropriate diagnostics and repairs before continuing.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Do "
                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_102.xml" xrefid="tp305010605">Test 5. Fuel Supply System Test</hotlnk>
                    " in the "
                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="s3050106">Performance Diagnostics</hotlnk>
                    " section of this manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <para>See the "
                <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050107.xml" xrefid="e3050107">Electronic Control Systems Diagnostics
                </hotlnk>
                " section of this manual or the applicable truck Circuit Diagram Manualand Service Manual when
                performing the following steps.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check all ECM and IDM related fuses.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Check all Battery, VIGNand ground connections for the ECM and IDM.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Monitor ECM powers and grounds with breakout box under operator complaint conditions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Monitor IDM powers and grounds with 12-Pin Breakout Harness under operator complaint
                    conditions.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If root cause has not been identified in previous steps, continue diagnosis by doing the
                    remaining tests in "
                    <hotlnk document="eges3052_E3050106.xml" xrefid="e3050106">Performance Diagnostics</hotlnk>
                    " section of this manual.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
